***************************************************************************
                              Coding Efficiently
***************************************************************************

is_clone check:
        The is_clone check is meant for objects that do not need to refer
        to their master object. It will prevent the code from setting the
        various functions, such as the set_long string, on that master
        object. The check should appear before ::reset(arg) is called,
        and should be entered as follows:

    if (!is_clone(this_object())) return;

        The is_clone check should appear in all cloned objects and
        monsters, unless the object's master object needs to actually
        do something/store information. (99% of objects do not.) It 
        should not be used in room files.

